cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR

This paper is about named entity recognition (NER) using a novel model architecture that incorporates hierarchical contextualized representation. The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The model also uses machine learning techniques such as BiLSTM and attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in the subfields of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques such as key-value memory network, which is a subfield of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper presents state-of-the-art results on three benchmark NER datasets, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
